</table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 441<br> <font color=#E9D756>(12/3/01 11:36:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auctions</span><hr size=1> I was looking for a few items last night and selling off others.  It was one of the most frustrating nights of all my time in Ebay Commons.  As a Tailor and Baker, I've spent lots of time there selling my wares.  But last night was awful.<br>
<br>
First, I kept getting people how much I was asking for one of the items I was looking to purchase.  I clearly started the line with WTB at first, and then switched to BUYING, but still kept getting tells from random_doormat_01.  What the hell is up with that?  Sure it was busy, but it's not that hard to see the line WTB or BUYING.  It was very annoying.<br>
<br>
Second,  the spam was ridiculous.  I turned all chat off except for /auc, and was still getting folks posting and reposting their auctions every 15-20 seconds.  One of the losers had a two line post that was on my screen three times at once, resulting in his one /auction being a third of my chat screen.  Another idiot kept posting his PC on ry-gorr arms every 20 seconds for five minutes.  He just didn't catch a clue when no one responded that no one either knew or cared.  He finally slowed down, but he still kept up the PC for 20 minutes.  It was hysterical seeing someone make a fool of themselves like that.<br>
<br>
