<br>
Finally, if you don't post a price in what you are selling, and the prospective buyer asks you how much, provide a price.  When you say &quot;Make offer,&quot; what you really mean is that &quot;I'm going to try and take advantage of you if you don't know what the item is really worth.&quot;  You will never hear from me again on the sale, as you've confirmed yourself as a scammer, although a mostly benign one.<br>
<br>
What really chaps my hide the most, is an item one of my alts was looking for was finally offered for sale by Tumyetoe, and I was compelled to buy it.  Probably what made me so grumpy last night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufierios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fierios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#E9D756>(12/3/01 12:01:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Auctions</span><hr size=1> The whole &quot;make offers&quot; deal could get controversial. There are those items, where there is an un sure value of it. e.g. anything after 60k doesn't really have a price set in stone. You can run a PC, and you'll end up getting a large range. I get pissed, when I say &quot;/auc WTS Item ABC, Make offers&quot; And I get tells &quot;Oooh, that's nice, how much?&quot; <br>
